<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-10-26T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-10-26T19:00:00-05:00" n="649" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d649">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113/1402: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Consul at Saigon (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_WHS1">Waterman</persName>)</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-10-26T19:00:00-05:00">October 26, 1932—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your despatch of August 8 concerning transit of goods through
                            Indo-China.</p>
                        <p>In the absence of a specific case, Department feels that it would be
                            inopportune to raise this question at least until commercial treaty
                            negotiations with France<note n="22" xml:id="d649fn22">See <ref target="frus1932v02#pg_195">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>,
                                    pp. 195</ref> ff.</note> have been concluded. Please report
                            fully with regard to French regulations and practices in respect of this
                            transit trade.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_CWR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>